  "Broker Comment" : "ON 10/1/2016, REGISTRANT, WITHOUT ADMITTING OR DENYING THE FINDINGS, ENTERED INTO A SETTLEMENT OF PUBLIC ADMINISTRATIVE AND CEASE-AND-DESIST PROCEEDINGS WITH THE SEC. NO CUSTOMER COMPLAINTS WERE INVOLVED AND NO RESTITUTION WAS ORDERED. IN DETERMINING TO ACCEPT THE OFFER, THE COMMISSION CONSIDERED VARIOUS REMEDIAL EFFORTS BY THE FIRM AND COOPERATION AFFORDED THE COMMISSION STAFF. SPECIFICALLY, THE FIRM REVISED ITS BEST EXECUTION AND PRINCIPAL TRANSACTIONS POLICIES AND PROCEDURES. FURTHER, THE FIRM RETAINED A CONSULTANT TO ASSIST IT IN DEVELOPING AND IMPLEMENTING POLICIES AND PROCEDURES REASONABLY DESIGNED TO PROMOTE THE FIRM'S COPMLIANCE WITH THE ADVISERS ACT, INCLUDING ITS BEST EXECUTION AND PRINICPAL TRANSACTION OBLIGATIONS."
